CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 14, 1946, pg. 17, reads: "Okay Vet's Confab - In a recent meeting in his office, Mayor David L. Lawrence put his stamp of approval on the Veterans Conference, being sponsored Dec. 15, by several civic organizations, in cooperation with the Urban League. Left to right are seated: Mrs. Edna Vaughn, NAACP; Miss Jean Zimmer, AVC. Standing: Walter Carter, American Legion; Charles Winbush, CIO Steelworker; Alvin Snyder, Urban League; Arthur S. Brown, VFW; and Charles W. Washington, Urban League official.  The meeting will be held at Warren Church. - Harris Photo"
TitMainTitle: Group portrait, seated from left: Pittsburgh Mayor David L. Lawrence, Edna Vaughn, Jean Zimmer; standing: Walter Carter, Charles Winbush, Alvin Snyder, Arthur S. Brown, and Charles  W. Washington, in mayor's office for meeting about veteran's conference
